GOAL: Create comprehensive tests for context alert functionality.

DEPENDS ON: T1324 (integration complete)

TEST FILES TO CREATE:
1. tests/unit/context-alert.bats - Unit tests for library functions
2. tests/integration/context-alert-integration.bats - End-to-end tests

UNIT TESTS (context-alert.bats):
```bash
@test "check_and_alert_context returns 0 when no session active" {
    # Remove .current-session
    # Run check_and_alert_context
    # Assert exit 0, no output
}

@test "check_and_alert_context returns 0 when status unchanged" {
    # Set up session
    # Set .context-state.json to warning
    # Set .context-last-alert to warning
    # Run check_and_alert_context
    # Assert exit 0, no output
}

@test "check_and_alert_context emits alert on threshold crossing" {
    # Set up session
    # Set .context-state.json to critical
    # Set .context-last-alert to warning (or none)
    # Run check_and_alert_context
    # Assert exit 1, stderr contains alert box
}

@test "alert output uses FACE UP format" {
    # Trigger alert
    # Assert stderr contains emoji, box characters, status
}
```

INTEGRATION TESTS:
```bash
@test "cleo complete triggers context alert" {
    # Start session, set up mock context state
    # Run cleo complete
    # Assert stderr contains alert
    # Assert stdout contains JSON (order matters!)
}
```

PERFORMANCE TEST:
- Verify alert check adds <50ms overhead to commands

